Tags.string 'Text': The albedo is a greyscale map and we use a blend overlay to mix color in. As we can have a variable amount of robots, we use a hue shift instead setting the color directly.
A mask is used to seperate primary, secondary and emissive colors
Roughness, metalic and AO are packed together in one texture using different channels.
This function is also used in the face material and outputs a mask and faces interior to look "solid" when a new bot is printed.
